has-text-align-none\">Not long after the <a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/480312/game-awards-2024-nominees-list-game-of-the-year\">Game Awards nominations</a> were announced on Monday, we at Polygon noticed something interesting happening in our web traffic. Readers were clicking from our story about the nominations through to reviews of some of the games that had been recognized \u2014 and they were doing so in surprisingly large numbers. Our <a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/reviews/24084564/balatro-review-poker-game-deck-building-roguelite\">review of indie card game <em>Balatro</em></a>, which was nominated for <a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/awards/450195/game-of-the-year-game-aw", "id": 1553262, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/awards/481955/game-awards-goty-nominations-2024-analysis", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 258, "source_url": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "In a tough year for video games, the Game Awards nominations give some cause for hope", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-20T14:00:00+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"Image: Blizzard Entertainment\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/11/Drakkisath_HS.webp?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-drop-cap has-text-align-none\">I\u2019ve never been a person who aspires to do \u201celite gamer\u201d stuff in video games. My favorite genres are point-and-click puzzle adventures and narrative role-playing games, I prefer to enjoy video games alone, and I\u2019m constitutionally noncompetitive. Given all that, you might wonder how I nevertheless spent eight years of my life playing <em>World of Warcraft</em>.\u00a0</p>\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">Perhaps it was because, early in the life of the storied MMO, it gave me a glimpse of what it might be like to have an elite level of skill, and have that skill recognized by other players. My elite gamer moment wasn\u2019t reaching ma", "id": 1553263, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/world-of-warcraft/480533/upper-blackrock-spire-kiting-general-hunter", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 258, "source_url": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "World of Warcraft gave me my one elite gamer moment: Kiting the General in Upper Blackrock Spire", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-20T13:59:07+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"Image: FromSoftware\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/11/eldenring-horseman.jpg?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">Kadokawa Corporation has confirmed <a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/news/481294/sony-fromsoftware-kadokawa-acquisition-talks\">a recent Reuters report</a> concerning a possible acquisition by Sony.</p>\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">The <a href=\"https://ssl4.eir-parts.net/doc/9468/ir_material7/240956/00.pdf\">official release</a>, \u201cNotice Regarding Media Articles,\u201d was uploaded to Kadokawa\u2019s investor relations portal Nov. 20. The full text reads:</p>\n\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote has-text-align-none is-layout-flow wp-block-quote-is-layout-flow\">\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">There are some articles on the acquisition of KADOKAWA Corporati", "id": 1553264, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/news/482003/kadokawa-fromsoftware-sony-playstation-dark-souls-elden-ring-anime-manga", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 258, "source_url": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "FromSoftware parent company confirms Sony\u2019s acquisition intent", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-20T12:41:57+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"A stock photo of the white Steam Deck\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/11/White-Steam-Deck.jpg?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=9.77890625,0,77.63046875,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">Earlier this month, Valve announced that it would be launching a new <a href=\"https://store.steampowered.com/steamdeck\">limited edition Steam Deck OLED</a>. The $679 handheld features the same hardware and specifications as its <a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/23952634/steam-deck-oled-limited-edition-translucent\">1 TB transparent model</a> from last year but with a matte-white finish. It is currently available to pre-order from Valve while supplies last.</p>\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">Purchases of the new Steam Deck are limited to one per Steam account, and just in case you were thinking about making some ", "id": 1552772, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/pre-order/479343/steam-deck-oled-limited-edition-white", "manual_status_code": 0, "p